**Nostr** (`extensions/nostr/src/channel.ts` lines 424-443)
```typescript
sendText: async ({ cfg, to, text, accountId }) => {
  const core = getNostrRuntime();
  const aid = accountId ?? DEFAULT_ACCOUNT_ID;
  const bus = activeBuses.get(aid);  // Must be running
  const tableMode = core.channel.text.resolveMarkdownTableMode({...});
  const message = core.channel.text.convertMarkdownTables(text, tableMode);
  const normalizedTo = normalizePubkey(to);
  await bus.sendDm(normalizedTo, message);
  return attachChannelToResult("nostr", { to: normalizedTo, messageId });
}
```

**Key differences:**
- IRC chunks text (delivery mode = "direct" + chunker function)
- Nostr has 4000 char limit (single message assumed)
- Both convert markdown tables before sending
- Record activity via `runtime.channel.activity.record()`

